    {
      "para_id": "p2",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "CCDH's Response to the Digital Fairness Act Consultation"
      ],
      "ordinal": 2,
      "text": "The Center for Countering Digital Hate (CCDH) appreciates the opportunity to contribute to the European Commission's work on the upcoming Digital Fairness Act (DFA). CCDH is an international non-profit research and advocacy organization with offices in Washington D.C., Brussels and London. CCDH conducts independent studies, campaigns for social media reform and advises lawmakers and regulators on the basis of our research.",
      "char_len": 426,
      "chunk_word_count": 62,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9644808743169399,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8591549295774648
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9733606557377049,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p3",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "CCDH's Response to the Digital Fairness Act Consultation"
      ],
      "ordinal": 3,
      "text": "The online world forms a core part of European citizens' daily lives. From reading the news and connecting with friends to discovering new music, European users are increasingly living digitally. Given the centrality of technology and platforms to everyday activities, the Digital Fairness Act is needed to update the European Union's consumer protection legislation and ensure it is fit for the digital age.",
      "char_len": 408,
      "chunk_word_count": 63,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9797687861271677,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8480392156862745
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9848265895953758,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p4",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "CCDH's Response to the Digital Fairness Act Consultation"
      ],
      "ordinal": 4,
      "text": "CCDH wholeheartedly welcomes the EU Commission's stated goal of addressing dark patterns and addictive design in the DFA. To meaningfully approach these issues, real changes are needed in the development, design and operation of online platforms. The implementation of algorithmic pluralism would allow for this profound rethinking of the online world, prioritizing users' well-being and their fundamental freedoms.",
      "char_len": 415,
      "chunk_word_count": 58,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9748603351955307,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8626506024096385
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9811452513966481,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p5",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 5,
      "text": "Recommender systems are harmful to consumers",
      "char_len": 44,
      "chunk_word_count": 6,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 1.0,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8863636363636364
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.45,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p6",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 6,
      "text": "The digital world is dominated by a few very large companies who control platforms' content, their moderation and the algorithms used. Algorithms are automated systems designed to amplify content in order to maximize user engagement. Specific metrics such as clicks, likes and content popularity are used to create personalized feeds for each individual user. Essentially, algorithms decide what information users have access to, they control the 'public square' of social media platforms.",
      "char_len": 489,
      "chunk_word_count": 72,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9736842105263158,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8548057259713702
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.980263157894737,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p7",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 7,
      "text": "The harms perpetrated by platforms and their recommender systems are well-documented. Notably, CCDH research has shown that TikTok's algorithm targets vulnerable teens with harmful content. Within minutes, TikTok's algorithm recommended eating disorder and self-harm content to newly established teen accounts. Teenagers were shown body image and",
      "char_len": 346,
      "chunk_word_count": 46,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9700996677740864,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.869942196531792
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9470191952750093,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p8",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 8,
      "text": "CCDH Center for Countering Digital Hote",
      "char_len": 39,
      "chunk_word_count": 6,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 1.0,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8717948717948718
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.45,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
