    },
    {
      "para_id": "p20",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 20,
      "text": "Users would be able to opt-in to personalized recommendations and pick which data points are used to inform the algorithm.",
      "char_len": 122,
      "chunk_word_count": 20,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9805825242718447,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8442622950819673
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5576591154261057,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p21",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 21,
      "text": "If the changes cannot be implemented, there should be clearly communicated reasons.",
      "char_len": 83,
      "chunk_word_count": 12,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9722222222222222,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8674698795180723
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.4291666666666667,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p22",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 22,
      "text": "The design and development choices should be made public by the VLOP so that they can be assessed by third parties.",
      "char_len": 115,
      "chunk_word_count": 21,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9894736842105263,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8260869565217391
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5796052631578947,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p23",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 23,
      "text": "Decentralize VLOPs’ absolute control over software, content moderation and curation by allowing other providers to curate algorithms.",
      "char_len": 133,
      "chunk_word_count": 17,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9743589743589743,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8796992481203008
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5071581196581196,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p24",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 24,
      "text": "Users would have access to multiple diverse feeds, enhancing their freedom to choose how their digital environment is constructed.",
      "char_len": 130,
      "chunk_word_count": 19,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9821428571428571,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8615384615384616
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5435515873015873,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p25",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 25,
      "text": "Platforms would need to allow interoperability with other algorithm providers, thus creating a true open marketplace for social media where businesses and new market entrants have an opportunity to compete.",
      "char_len": 206,
      "chunk_word_count": 30,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9887005649717514,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8592233009708737
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7165254237288137,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p26",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 26,
      "text": "Either operationalization of algorithmic choice would have a real impact on the harms the DFA seeks to address, including addictive design, spams, dark patterns and disinformation.",
      "char_len": 180,
      "chunk_word_count": 26,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9741935483870968,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8611111111111112
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6445340501792115,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p27",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 27,
      "text": "User agency over recommender systems means the ability to opt out of addictive designs and dark patterns. Users would be able to choose how content is presented to them – for example, in ‘chronological order’ or showing ‘trusted sources only’. This would break the dependency loop social media platforms have created which manipulate users into choosing unhealthier experiences. Giving the European consumers the right to choose how to design their online environment, and to opt-out of default addictive design, could reduce many of social media’s harms and while giving user’s the freedom to customize to their specific needs.",
      "char_len": 628,
      "chunk_word_count": 99,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9717514124293786,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8455414012738853
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.978813559322034,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p28",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Algorithmic Pluralism"
      ],
      "ordinal": 28,
      "text": "Agency over recommender systems can also prevent disinformation and harmful content from being pushed onto users. Options to downrank, exclude low-quality sources or choose “trust-enhancing” algorithms that have been vetted by independent bodies would allow for a trustworthy, information-integral feed. Such changes would transform the users’ online experience by reducing recommender systems’ ability to cause harm through the amplification of viral mis- and disinformation.",
      "char_len": 476,
      "chunk_word_count": 64,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9685230024213075,
        "digit": 0.0,
